block.documentation:
The Structure & Mechanisms Subsystem provides the foundational framework for the AOMS, supporting all other subsystems and maintaining the physical integrity of the spacecraft. The Primary Frame houses the manufacturing, power, and communication subsystems, while the Antenna Deployment Mechanism and Array Deployment Mechanism allow the spacecraft to unfold critical components after launch.
The Solar Array Gimbal and Antenna Gimbal are mechanisms that allow fine control over the positioning of the solar arrays and antennas to maximize efficiency in power generation and communication. Additionally, the Separation Subsystem handles the release of modules or components as needed during mission phases, such as docking or deorbiting activities.
